Let the editor re-apply a slot whose previous apply timed out

When a slot's apply hits MQTT-response timeout, HA storage is
already updated but the lock didn't receive the push: slot.status
becomes "timeout" and the slot is out of sync. Opening the editor
showed the same name/pin/enabled the storage already has, the form
read as unchanged, and the Apply button stayed disabled, leaving
the user with no way to retry.

Carry slot.status into the editor's original-slot snapshot, treat
status == "timeout" as a reason to enable the save button and
label it Apply even with no field changes, and skip update_slot
when the form is unchanged so the retry path is just apply_slot.

